// PSA; my feb 5th class with my friend was cancelled, everyone who purchased a ticket has been refunded. I apologize for the inconvenience. I used this time to really consider what I have to offer as far as education. What can I offer to anyone choosing to invest in my classes? I had to really shut my imposter syndrome down, and really look at what I have to offer. And aside from doing great haircuts, I know I’m good at color, color correcting, consulting, networking, leading, photography, formulating, all the things it takes to be a successful hairstylist in this industry. And I say that as humbly as possible without trying to seem like an arrogant stylist. So this year I’m going to create a more diverse curriculum to be able to offer the growing stylist the confidence to take on a multitude of clients and be fearless in the work environment. //

// tomorrow I will be teaching my first cutting class @onyxonmadison . I remember coming to the salons grand opening party on December of 2021 and thinking there was no way they would want me there. Never feeling good enough has always been my biggest vice. The photographer asked Daniel & Chaie for a picture of the team, I stood still not knowing yet I would be working alongside them. @danielmbeauty called me over to take the photo with the team. I felt like I just won high school prom queen. 🤣 I can’t believe I’ve been here for a little over a year already. So grateful to be here and thankful to Daniel & @chaiedejesus  for the opportunities they have given me. I strive to elevate my craft to be up to par with you guys. & a very special thank you to @yvettehlopez all the work you do behind the scenes that goes unnoticed sometimes because as hairdressers we get so wrapped up in being behind the chair. I appreciate you ❤️ Yall are inspiring or whateva 🤣😘 // #444

// remember that time we were out of work for 3 months? Opening up a suite, to create a comfortable and safe space to be able to create and take clients? Being threatened to have our licenses taken away if we were caught working, but had no income coming in? Having to sneak clients in to the salon, trying to find a little bit of normalcy in life by trying to stay creative. This was only about two years ago but I feel like my trauma response was to ignore it happened. I was looking for a specific picture through my archive and I realized I didn’t want to look back at some of these pictures because it brings me back to these feelings of uncertainty. Of fear. But I realized that once again the hair industry and the art of hair pulled me through another difficult chapter in my life. Just feeling so grateful to be in this industry, and to have the support I have had from clients, colleagues, and family. ✨//

// looking for 4 MUSES. If you  or someone you know is looking for a new look, someone going through a new chapter in their life and just needs something different with their hair, a new haircut, a new color, a new shift in life. I’d like to meet with them and possibly discuss going on this journey together. This will be a complimentary service/ services. I’d like to photograph and video if the person is comfortable. If you’d read this far, I’m looking for any kind of hair texture, any kind of starting point I.e. box dye/ color correction. Any length; long to short. Any age, any WOMAN. I’ve been so blessed with all the women in my life & today this is my way of showing gratitude to all of the women that have shown up for me, supported me, & believed in me. So please tag & share with someone and match me up with my next muse ✨ //

// I was feeling a little down because of a couple looks I had to re-do. My goal is always to make clients feel the best they possibly can and when I get that dreaded message of clients not being happy i feel like the worst stylist ever and wonder why I’m still doing what I’m doing. Oh that’s right cus I have bills to pay. Lmao BUT coming to Pasadena has really challenged me to grow and try to perfect my craft as much as possible. There is SOOOO many talented stylist that surround me and the competition is SEVERE girl. It’s easy to feel like the least talented stylist there is. But if all my years in the industry have taught me anything is to not forget how far you have come, how hard you have worked, & to always be a student. //
